0.7.0 phase 3: deliver.js chunked-delivery primitive

Pulls the multi-chunk send loop out of polygram.js's handleMessage
into a reusable lib/deliver.js. handleMessage's old code:

  for (const chunk of chunkText(rest)) {
    try { await tg(...); } catch (err) { logger.error(...); }
  }

mixed delivery concerns (chunking, reply linkage, error tolerance)
into the streaming-finalize path, which made the new "preview-becomes-
final" flow (Phase 5) hard to express cleanly. With deliverReplies as
a pr
